# Graphify Context Rule

Use Graphify before asking Cursor to scan broad raw directories. Prefer task-specific Graphify queries before broad file search or large edits.

Graph reports may exist at:

```text
docs/graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
backend/graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
frontend/src/graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
tests/graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
```

Graph JSON files may exist under matching `graphify-out/graph.json` folders.

To query a graph, first `cd` into the mapped folder, then run `graphify query`:

```bash
cd /home/tjrpirateking/projects/WritingAssistantApplication/docs
graphify query "Which roadmap specs define approved memory canon pages and OMI candidate boundaries?"
```

Use `graphify path "<A>" "<B>"` for relationship questions and `graphify explain "<concept>"` for focused concepts when those are more direct than a query.

Do not require reading huge raw directories before checking Graphify reports or queries. If Graphify is missing, there is no `graphify-out/graph.json`, or a query fails, report the failure and continue conservatively with targeted source-of-truth file reads.

After modifying runtime code files, run `graphify update .` to keep the graph current when Graphify is available. Documentation/configuration-only tasks do not require graph updates.
